('100062409', NULL, 'users/100005562/alex-heaton', 'Sure. I was referring to videos 15 and 16 from Lesson 1. These were the only videos done by Dr. Feist, so I was a bit worried that he would always do them in that style unless we gave some feedback. All the other videos I have watched so far in this course have been "Udacity style" with the pen, writing, etc.\n\nWhen I said "powerpoint" I was referring to the facts that those two videos (1) had typed words, (2) had words that would appear on cue as if someone was clicking to the next slide, and (3) did not include any pen or hand writing on the screen, pointing at parts of the screen, or marking up parts of the screen.\n\nPerhaps I am just afraid of change (having taken many a Udacity course before), but I do think there is something about the normal Udacity style that better captures and maintains my attention.', '03 Jun ''13, 22:30', '100062389'),
