('100062771', NULL, 'users/113836624/halfknot', '@Samarth \nI''m not sure I understand what you''re asking me. The difference between them is pointed out in the quotation I pasted from Wikipedia. You can be introverted without being shy, and shy without being introverted. There''s no obvious correlation between them.\n\nI don''t see how people "may understand it better this way" if they understand it completely wrong. Either giving a technical definition (e.g. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extraversion_and_introversion#Introversion) or just explaining in a few words what introversion is (and maybe pointing out how it''s different from shyness just to make it clear) would have been perfect. Personally, I wouldn''t have minded if they only said "introversion" because people would google what it means if they didn''t know. However, if you say "introversion or shyness" this makes people believe they are the same thing, so no one bothers to google, thus contributing to spreading false information. \n\nSorry for being so persistent about what others might see as a minor thing, but I have high expectations from Udacity as all the previous courses I''ve done were of high quality, thus I warmly recommended the website to a lot of friends, and I don''t want them to be disappointed as well.', '04 Jun ''13, 05:58', '100062588'),
('100062782', NULL, 'users/100004223/tung-nguyen', 'If teaching is all about the material, teachers would not exist. Only books should do. Udacity is trying to revolutionize the way people learn online. So it''s our privilege to provide feedback to the professors at San Jose State Univ. They''re doing a good job, but more is needed.', '04 Jun ''13, 06:35', '100062778'),
('100062796', NULL, 'users/116220715/rohan-29', 'Absolutely, I guess my perspective comes from the fact that this is my first MOOC class in Udacity. I found it way better than learning from books. However I found courses at Codecademy equally stimulating, where neither a powerpoint is used or someone writing on a tablet.\n\nKaizen is always appreciated :)', '04 Jun ''13, 07:27', '100062778'),
