('100067208', '100062718', 'users/118578353/susan-snycerski', 'We do not have a textbook, however, there will be reading that needs to be completed for some of our lessons. For example, in Lesson 3, which is coming next, there are pdf documents in the Instructor Notes section that are required reading. We also have pdf document for other lessons as well. So, although you need not read a textbook there will be some additional reading required.', '09 Jun ''13, 16:44', NULL),
('100067237', '100066618', 'users/116520495/steven-205', 'Although the researcher may not know who is in which group, when the analysis is conducted, the researcher will still know which data represents each group.  As far as researcher bias goes, this is why psychology has an ethical code set for the by the American Psychological Association.  The other wonderful thing about psychological research is that it is peer-reviewed, meaning that research that is published is accessible to other researchers as well.  If a researcher publishes results that seem funky, another researcher can come along and run the same experiment to either support or not support the initial researchers results!  There have been cases where researchers have modified the results to their liking, but they are usually discovered through the peer-reviewed process!', '09 Jun ''13, 17:39', NULL),
