('100078171', NULL, 'users/117873581/beatriz-16', '" so blue eye colored parent and brown eye colored parent, will always have a brown eye color child, (if eye color was determined by one gene, which it is not)"\n\nNot necessarily. \nYou have two alleles, one from dad and one from mom, but each of them also have two alleles the same way. The brown-eyed parent can have one blue allele (hidden because of the brown one), so there is simply 50% chance that he gives the brown allele to their child (and the child would have brown eyes) and 50% chance he gives the blue allele, so the child would have blue eyes even if one of the parents doesn''t.', '25 Jun ''13, 17:32', '100067934'),
