('100079324', NULL, 'users/120686583/chadwick-4', 'Very cool. I think a distinction has to be made between "evolution (change) from natural selection" and "macro-evolution" based on very little evidence and a whole lot of inferences and leaps of logic. General acceptance is cultural and it is easy to accept, but not all scientists agree, because it is not based on the same power behind the conclusions for micro-evolution. Likewise, "God" is everywhere and law binds everything together, but religion is cultural. For an interesting problem, prove scientifically that the number one exists. It requires logic and cannot be scientifically proven, yet without it, we would not be doing science. ;)\n\nThank you. :)', '27 Jun ''13, 12:36', '100079162'),
