('100098592', NULL, 'users/129034155/sylvia-9', 'Yes, there are some readings about homosexualtity in animals. I picked some public ones. But there are books on the subject as well (Bruce Bagemihl - Biological Exuberance: Animal Homosexuality And Natural Diversity). There are of course some critics, too. But then, that is the case in any open discussion. \n\nFor example:\nhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-1279241/Lesbian-albatrosses-gay-giraffes-open-minded-penguins-So-animals-really-gay.html\nhttp://www.yalescientific.org/2012/03/do-animals-exhibit-homosexuality/\nNot as trustworthy, but there is an entry in wikipedia (english) on the subject.', '01 Aug ''13, 19:18', '100098584'),
('100098610', NULL, 'users/100000724/hisham-showeir', 'I have skimmed the Mail Online article, and I believe researchers have come up with something that we should dedicate some time to.', '01 Aug ''13, 20:02', '100098584'),
('100098614', NULL, 'users/129034155/sylvia-9', 'What is important to note, is that animals show homosexual behavior - we can''t say that an animal is 100% gay and we don''t know why animals show those behaviors. But I think that the mere existance of animal homosexual behavior should be read as a sign that nature is much more broad than some humans would like to think.', '01 Aug ''13, 20:08', '100098584'),
