('100098838', '100097439', 'users/129034155/sylvia-9', 'So I just got to this section and did the IAT.\nI''m German too, I don''t have much contact with "African-Americans" or "black" people in general and my results are "No preferences".\n\nI get what you mean by not being exposed to the "traditional black/white" theme of the test. Evenso this doesn''t mean "we" don''t have any prejudice against "black" people. Prejudice don''t form only because of real experiences we have with people but how those groups are represented in media and such playes a role too. And it might be that we even generalize further - I mean if I have prejudices about "non-white" people I''m exposed to in a pretty regular way, I might extend those prejudices to this case of "black" people. For example one common prejudice in Germany regarding immigrants is that they "don''t work and live on social support", with this as a basis I might answer "people of color are lazy" because I use one stereotype as a basis for judging something I don''t yet have a certain opinion on. Hope this makes some sense... \nI don''t mean to say your results truely repesent you but that they might hold some truth. \n\nJust one last thing: \nI did the gender IAT too and I''m "prejudiced against women in the sciences" - Well, I am a woman and I hold a master''s degree in engineering.', '02 Aug ''13, 10:24', NULL),
('100098855', NULL, 'users/129034155/sylvia-9', 'You''re very welcome.', '02 Aug ''13, 11:10', '100098846'),
