('100098874', '100081000', 'users/114763343/queency', 'The movie "thank you for smoking" may also be helpful ... or at least amusing.', '02 Aug ''13, 11:48', NULL),
('100098876', NULL, 'users/129034155/sylvia-9', 'Okay - few things I want to say:\n\n\n\nYou know the saying "Never is never right and always is always wrong"?\nYour argument is that my examples don''t work because they are based on "lack of information" in one case ( "black" discrimination) and "a lot of information" in the homosexual case. This seems strange - we still don''t know why people are homosexual, so we have too much information? \n\n\nAnd if I wanted to take a crass (and probably wrong) view of your reproduction argument, I could ask you: "Why do you think homosexuality isn''t part of the longterm reproduction system in the human species?"\nA theory could be that homosexuality evolved because the individuals have the ability to produce offspring that maybe 10. Generations down the line could cause some problems - of any kind, be it too many "geniuses", "fertility problems" and so on.  Here I''m stressing the "fertile" part of your argument.\n\n\n\nNow I want to be clear - this is not a theory I personally believe but it is possible - no one knows!\n\n\nHomosexual behavior in animals\nAs you can see in the comment I made on my answer - I''m not saying that just because animals do it - we should too. But for whatever reasons these behaviors exist - maybe just for bonding or because a compatible mate isn''t available - they do show that homosexual behaviors have a place in many species. And they seem to serve a function, which functions we don''t know yet. So why should we consider them "bad" when a human uses them to bond with other organisms of his species? Especially since we do have quite a few behaviors in common with other non-human animals - e.g. taking care of offspring - that we don''t consider wrong just because animals do it too.\n', '02 Aug ''13, 12:02', '100098860'),
('100098889', NULL, 'users/100057011/muammar', 'Thank you, Sylvia, for your rapid responses).\nWe don''t know a lot about many things, for example about many illnesses. But if we face this illness, we have to say NOW, would we treat it or it''s normal? First of all we look at the consequences. And nowadays we know a lot of disadvantages of homosexuality, but only few advantages. Like an alcohol. It''s a drug, as it was said in this course and there are a lot of disadvantages, but there are a few advantages too. If man have addiction, we treat him. What is an addiction in homosexuality? I really don''t know).\nAnd your hypothesis about "maybe in future it will be a super-beneficial" just a hypothesis. We live now and we have to do something now.', '02 Aug ''13, 13:00', '100098860'),
