('100109418', NULL, 'users/100045870/afgak', 'If we do a study and see that there is correlation between A and B, then that does not imply causation. For instance, both A and B may have been caused by UNKNOWN factor C, which was not in our study. We can''t group it with anything because we haven''t included it in our study and have no sure idea what it is. \n\nIf we make a NEW study where we check for the correlation between A, B and C, then any correlation we find may still be because of unknown factor D, and so on, or again, just by chance. \n\nIt is not until we do an experiment in which we control the presence or non-presence of a factor, that we can conclusively prove causation.', '01 Sep ''13, 08:30', '100109376'),
