('100114865', NULL, 'users/105298481/bonifacio', 'I would say that "If you''re depressed you have no emotions" is a too strong statement to be made. The lighter levels of depression are filled with sadness and other negative emotions. But down the deeper and stronger levels of depression you really stop feeling those. You just feel... nothing. Or maybe only apathy and a total lack of connection with the world.', '20 Sep ''13, 10:43', '100103381'),
