('100180414', NULL, 'users/100104209/marcus', 'Hi there philip,\nthe example(richard lewontin 1974) illustrates what happens when variables are confounded. They don''t tell you anything about the way things work. that is the point. In the example you wouldn''t know what has to be done first, what the time intervalls were within anything could work together etc..............).\nThe point is the functional aspect you can''t overview by an exclusive view such as  shared or non-shared. Or such as genetics or environment. It''s always both and the variables work in both ways which makes it even more complicated. So you have to ask better questions.', '09 May ''14, 10:57', '100162312'),
