('100073313', 'What have we learner about infant and child cognitive development since Piaget? For example about deceprion?', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 05 Development - Social development', 'I understand that much has been learned about infant and child cognitive development in the years since Piaget.  Two examples are that our estimate of "inborn" and infant cognitive abilities has increased in recent years. Also experiments have been done on children''s ability to "deceive" and their lack of  theory of mind skills.', 'users/100002307/ira-laefsky-1', '18 Jun ''13, 23:13', 437, 1, 2),
