('100074838', 'The Spinal Cord', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 03 Biology of Behavior - Startling dog', 'What role does the spinal cord have in a person''s body except as a way to transmit messages between neurotransmitters to help with the structure of someone''s body?', 'users/115265620/drew-37', '20 Jun ''13, 23:04', 163, 1, 1),
('100074844', 'Somatic vs. Autonomic Nervous System', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 03 Biology of Behavior - Nervous system parts', 'when we think of the nervous system, is it comprised of every single nerve cell in the body, and no other types of cells? I am a little confused about this in regard to the peripheral nervous system. Do the somatic nervous system and the autonomic nervous system comprise of the same cells, but are just about two different functions the cells have, or are there different cells for each system?', 'users/115265620/drew-37', '20 Jun ''13, 23:15', 239, 0, 0),
('100074851', 'Neurons in the Brain', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 03 Biology of Behavior - The Amazing Brain in Lauren pets Sputnik', 'Where is the signal from that is sent to the motor cortex to allow for the action? Do the neurons just fire when someone decides they want to do something and in response to the decision?', 'users/115265620/drew-37', '20 Jun ''13, 23:24', 177, 0, 1),
('100074868', 'Where do we feel emotional pain?', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 04 Problem Set - Problem 07', 'Hi, The video teaches that the same area in our brain is activated in both phisical and emotional pain.  When we cut ourselves, we feel the pain in and around the cut. But where do we feel emotional pain?Where do the motor neurons take the signal? Or is it a different process than sensory-brain-motor?', 'users/121166559/iulia-5', '21 Jun ''13, 00:14', 186, 4, 1),
('100074938', 'Little mistake here', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 03 Problem Set - Problem 19', 'I think there is a little mistake here.\nMothers whom have been given the diet with the high amount of methylation nutrition ( such as folic acid, beets, onion, garlic) breed  skinny brown children. In the lecture it was presented visa verse. ', 'users/121618812/mostafa-17', '21 Jun ''13, 04:53', 300, 3, 1),
('100074977', 'You should mention Motion Parallax', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 04 Sensation and Perception - Monocular cues', 'It''s also one of the most important monocular cues \nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monocular_vision#Monocular_cues  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monocular_vision#Monocular_cues', 'users/116169258/emanuele-7', '21 Jun ''13, 07:49', 271, 1, 0),
('100074995', 'Atheists may skip a step.', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 05 Development - Five stages', 'Hi, I don''t think all of these stages apply to everyone. I don''t think atheists would go through a bargaining stage (despite some people''s belief that "there''s no atheists in the foxhole"). Any opinions on this?', 'users/121166559/iulia-5', '21 Jun ''13, 09:10', 451, 5, 6),
('100075005', 'A suggestion for the team', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 05 Problem Set - Problem 11', 'Hi, Sometimes it''s really hard to remember essential words (like the one being asked about here) if it hasn''t been written down, especially for foreigners like me. In these situations, would it be possible to also write down the word as you''re saying it? It''d be greatly appreciated. Thanks!', 'users/121166559/iulia-5', '21 Jun ''13, 09:34', 404, 13, 2),
('100075012', 'That''s only one type of myopia', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 04 Sensation and Perception - Nearsightedness and the eye', 'You only mentioned lenticular myopia, which is when the index of refraction of the lens is out of whack. There''s also axial myopia, when the eye is too long and the focal point doesn''t go to the retina.', 'users/100090696/larry-b', '21 Jun ''13, 09:54', 187, 2, 0),
('100075044', 'I don''t get this! I think the expected answer is incorrect.', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 04 Sensation and Perception - Depth Perception 2', 'Here is how i can logically deduce that the truck labeled 1 is the largest. I made a reasonable assumption that the grass section next to the tires is a rectangular one. The size of the wheel of truck 3 was less than that of the width of the grass whereas\nthe size of the wheel of truck 1 was greater than that of the width of the grass. The width of the grass remains the same because it''s a rectangle.  Since the truck sizes are proportional to the size of their respective wheels, I can conclude that truck 1 is bigger. Can anyone explain how am i wrong?', 'users/114411955/swagat', '21 Jun ''13, 11:07', 299, 1, 5),
