('100100635', 'This might be an oversimplification...', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 11 Motivation and Emotion - Maslow''s hierarchy', 'Hello! I think that Maslow''s hierarchy is of great use as a heuristic, but a strong oversimplification of human behavior... If it was true, why did, for example, cinemas run in Germany immediately after World War II? Best regards,\nJulien Caussin ', 'users/117588655/julirn', '06 Aug ''13, 13:52', 308, 1, 5),
