('100114994', 'Marriage differences between our parents/ and nowadays', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 05 Development - Parents age for marriage', 'Well, my mom was about 20 when she married, and my dad was about 28, and even though my mom got married pretty young, I want to assume that I''d be getting married one day at say age 25. When I have formed a career. Yet again, times were way different and didn''t have as much technological advances as we do now.', 'users/147761445/alejandra-20', '20 Sep ''13, 23:00', 547, 0, 13),
('100115004', '3 distinct attachment styles', 'null', 'I think the 3 distinct attachment styles are very interesting! However, I wonder if a baby could be Avoidant Attachment or Anxious Attachment even if the parent shows much warmth and loving towards him/her.  In other words, is the behavior based solely on temperament or is it a combination of temperament and treatment by the parent? Also, could the baby grow out of this behavior? Is it possible for an Avoidant attachment baby to become a warm and affectionate person in the future?  Or, on the other hand, could a Secure attachment baby grow up to be a cold and non-affectionate person in the future? ', 'users/147803011/allison-42', '21 Sep ''13, 01:42', 107, 0, 1),
