('100135084', 'assessing an animal''s personality + what about non animal organisms'' personality', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 13 Personality - Research on animal personality', 'How can animal''s personality traits be assessed ? Would anyone have an example of how to assess the agreableness of a guppy for instance ?\nLinks to research papers on this topic would be appreciated :)\nThanks !   PS : What about the personality of invertebrates, or even bacteria ? Where would you put the limit for organisms-with-personality (if there is one) ?', 'users/152716505/lena-15', '13 Dec ''13, 18:58', 106, 1, 0),
('100135194', 'Not speaking the native tongue', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 09 Language and Thought - Language taken for granted', 'I''ve been in the situation Dr. S described, and if you are trying to communicate, it''s very frustrating. However, if you don''t have to speak to anyone, it''s very liberating. You are almost incapable of caring about what other people are saying.  ', 'users/112631768/rick-3', '14 Dec ''13, 13:04', 92, 0, 0),
('100135268', 'Why isn''t Canine Psychology a possible real subfield?', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 01 What Is Psychology - Psychology and animals', 'I would like to know the answer for the above question because animals, to my knowledge, can do a lot more than we can actually think. Like the video itself talks about rats, dolphins, etc. I''ve heard dogs can sense earthquakes and ghosts (if the exist). So why not? They are living beings too!', 'users/184472414/ankur-39', '15 Dec ''13, 02:20', 194, 1, 2),
