('100199972', 'I heard you could cut DNA', 'Intro to Psychology - Lesson 03 Biology of Behavior - Genetic basis for behavior', 'I heard about restriction enzymes that can cut desirable strands of DNA. And then we can replace it with some other strand. So I was wondering that for a particular trait to be expressed in grown humans, do we have to do this to every cell with DNA in it. Or we could just do this to the cell  where the gene is expressed. Lastly, is it actually possible to do this with a zygote?????', 'users/137470381/prudhvi-1', '28 Jun ''14, 05:27', 157, 0, 0),
