('100063098', '100062977', 'users/117578412/greg-feist', 'Yes, and it is co-authored by one of your instructors (Feist), so it matches the material in the class closely. \nit is at https://create.mcgraw-hill.com/shop/#/catalog/details/?isbn=9781121842175\n~Greg Feist', '04 Jun ''13, 13:37', 0),
('100063100', '100062835', 'users/117578412/greg-feist', 'Problem sets are credit/no credit and credit is given to any and all who get a 75% or above on the problem sets. \n~Greg Feist (instructor)', '04 Jun ''13, 13:39', 3),
('100063105', '100062184', 'users/117578412/greg-feist', 'Actually, my PhD is in Personality psychology and introversion is a basic dimension of personality. Regardless of what Wikipedia says, it is simply not accurate to divorce shyness from introversion. Shyness is one of the key components to introversion, but it is not the only one. So be careful about using Internet sources with authority, because just because it''s on the Internet, doesn''t make it valid. This is key lesson in critical thinking. But I am glad to see this generated discussion, but I want to dispel any myths that shyness is not correlated with introversion. It is! \nBut it is true, also that shyness and introversion are NOT synonymous and if that was implied in the question, that is wrong. \n~Greg Feist (instructor)', '04 Jun ''13, 13:44', 12),
('100063111', '100061918', 'users/117578412/greg-feist', 'yes, it is because behaviorist don''t believe in personality traits as explanations; only observable behaviors.\n~Greg Feist (instructor)', '04 Jun ''13, 13:49', 6),
('100063130', '100062962', 'users/117586419/armando-maximo', 'En la parte inferior del video hay un cuadro que dice cc, ah puedes seleccionar los subttulos, aunque todava no estn disponibles en espaol. El subtitulaje lo hacen voluntarios, puedes entrar a la pgina de amara y ver los videos que se estn subtitulando:\nhttp://www.amara.org/en/teams/udacity/\nSaludos.', '04 Jun ''13, 14:08', 0),
