('100064399', '100062184', 'users/117578412/greg-feist', 'Class: \nThis is a great discussion!! Just what we wanted out of our course. \nI agree completely that shyness is not synonymous with introversion and we don''t want to imply that it is. But that doesn''t mean they are unrelated. What I still claim though is the argument that shyness and introversion are completely separate is simply not true. That may be Cain''s definition (and I was interviewed by Cain for her book) but do remember that she is actually not a psychologist. That doesn''t mean what she says is not true (I really like the thesis of her book, that there are many positive qualities to being introverted), but it does mean she is not trained in the science of personality psychology. \nAlso, I am most heartened by the discussion of critical thinking and evaluating the source of information. PhDs are not infallible by any means. We all make mistakes. It just means they have done a lot of reading and thinking about a given topic, and had to conduct original empirical research and defend it to a panel of experts. Some topics, especially in the social sciences, are open to debate and I am glad to see Personality creating such passion in students! \nWhat I like most of this is the critical evaluation of sources of information-the best skill possible you can take away from a class with! Keep it up!\n~Greg Feist', '05 Jun ''13, 19:17', 4),
