('100065045', '100064960', 'users/100042256/tobias-kuster', 'This should not be a problem if the test interface is sufficiently simple. Everybody should be able to click a button with the mouse, or to press some key on the keyboard, and if not, a short introduction should suffice. Alternatively, you could still use some special hardware setup, e.g., just a computer monitor and a big red game show buzzer button.\nI think the main distinction was that the actual measurement should better be done with a computer, since this will be more objective and accurate and not as error prone as a researcher with a stop watch. Consider the reaction time example: If you use stop watches, the measured reaction time is the sum of the participant''s reaction time following the color change, and the researcher''s reaction time following the participant''s reaction.', '06 Jun ''13, 14:10', 9),
