('100066189', '100064815', 'users/100004223/tung-nguyen', 'Coworkers are samples that need to be randomized from the population. In studies, it''s required that  every workers are picked and treated equally. The other variables must be controlled so that  it has no influence on the outcome of the dependent variable. \nFor example, if we pick an introvert and extrovert and assign them into two groups - the experimental and the control. The introvert may report no happiness at all after receiving a high five from even a sexy girl like Lauren, while the extrovert, who is naturally happy around people, is very easy to get upbeat with just a nice eye-contact from her. That''s a big flaw to draw conclusion from this.', '08 Jun ''13, 00:14', 3),
