('100068550', '100068498', 'users/113259599/drcookie', 'Given the assumptions set up in the scene, it''s not possible to be both. In this case brown eye color is dominant over blue, so the blue allele is completely masked; in other words there''s 0% chance of having a blue-eyed offspring. As noted in another forum post (and in the following video), eye color is actually polygenic, though brown generally seems dominant, though not always.\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eye_color', '11 Jun ''13, 18:39', 2),
