('100069456', '100069411', 'users/116520495/steven-205', 'Well lets take a look:\nThe location of the study could affect the number of drowning deaths if it were a large body of water (e.g. lake, river, or ocean)\nThe number of people swimming could affect the number of drowning deaths.  For example, if the study were conducted on a warm beach where lots of people like to swim versus a body of water that is very cold where rarely no one swims frequently.\nClimate could affect whether or not more people eat ice cream cones or swim.  For example, the number of ice cream cones eaten could be different in hot versus cold places.\nThe population could contribute to the number of ice cream cones eaten and the number of people swimming.  For example where there is a larger population, more people probably eat ice cream cones and swim.  \nHope that helps!', '13 Jun ''13, 00:34', 1),
