('100069464', '100069408', 'users/116520495/steven-205', 'Great question! No, ice cream cone consumption does not cause drowning deaths! But there is a correlation between the two, meaning that in certain populations, as more ice cream cones are eaten, more drowning deaths may occur.  Can you think of something that is related to the two that may contribute to the correlation? Heat may be one possibility.  Hope that helps!', '13 Jun ''13, 00:50', 2);
