('100070237', '100070021', 'users/100000364/michael-button', 'Ben, I think you are mixed up a bit here. In Unit 02-21, the two types of measurement are OBJECTIVE and SUBJECTIVE.  Under objective measures , there are physiological methods like measuring pulse rate, blood pressure or sweating.  In subjective measurement the people are asked to report how they feel about something.  I hope this helps.', '14 Jun ''13, 06:47', 8),
('100070267', '100069934', 'users/100000364/michael-button', 'Francis, the sympathetic n.s. is a subset of the peripheral n.s.\nPeripheral Nervous System :\n\n\nAutonomic\n   Sympathetic\n   Parasympathetic\n\n\n\nSomatic\n\n\nSo Peripheral Nervous System would not be exact. enough.', '14 Jun ''13, 08:32', 1),
