('100071106', '100069584', 'users/115794268/naomi-13', 'Having taken general psychology years ago, I can tell you now that you''re taking the wrong course if you''re looking for information on how the particular processes discussed evolved.  And the evolution of a nervous system probably becomes a lengthier discussion if you branch out from humans to all mammals.  That seems like a course in itself.  Plus, bear in mind that this is an introductory psychology course.  I imagine that we''re probably getting what is actually a very brief overview of psychology as a whole.  It''s probably the case that each lesson we get every week probably have entire courses devoted to further expanding on the information we''re getting now.', '15 Jun ''13, 12:30', 0),
