('100071262', '100070760', 'users/114069660/deanna-1', 'A confounding variable is a variable that effects the independent variable being studied and potentially effects the result of the study.  A more thorough explanation is here:  http://www.alleydog.com/glossary/definition.php?term=Confounding%20Variable', '15 Jun ''13, 18:00', 3),
