('100071870', '100064455', 'users/100015591/snoopy', 'Yes, i suppose the ''no-caffeine'' group is the placebo group.\nJust think the placebo group will get decaffeinated coffee: it tastes like coffee and people will be thinking they''re having coffee and caffeine, but they aren''t, actually.\nCaffeine group will receive regular coffee.\nThe best conditions for this kind of test are when the groups ignore what group they are into, or ignore the test is taking place at all: in this case everyone will behave just as if there was no difference at all between coffee and decaffeinated coffee.\nbye,\nSnoopy', '16 Jun ''13, 19:24', 1),
