('100072607', '100072456', 'users/100012341/jeff-scott', 'It''s kind of crazy they drop this stuff in that unit without explaining what they mean by "genetically identical mice with different mothers".\nSo-called genetically identical mice are developed through systematic inbreeding of brother-sister pairs. The technique of doing so was developed by Clarence Little. Little was an interesting guy, he was also notorious for advocating the forced sterilization and/or euthanization of non-white, poor and otherwise disadvantaged people, and others he felt were undesirable. (His advocacy and testimony resulted in states passing legislation resulting in the widespread involuntary sterilization of african americans and american indians.)  He was also famous for his militant advocacy of claims and "scientific" testimony that smoking cigarettes absolutely does not cause cancer, testimony for which the tobacco industry paid him and made him rich.\nBack to those mice, so if you inbreed mice with their siblings for 20 generations, you generate mice that are so genetically similar that you can continue to breed them and get essentially identical mice with no variations due to mother-father differences. They don''t actually have identical DNA though, just similar enough to produce this effect. In particular, they will be homozygous at all loci, which means they have identical alleles from mother and father at each loci, so there''s no variation in the genes they pass to their offspring. Pair them with another with the same configuration and you can systematically reproduce offspring. You could do the same with humans, if you were as insanely an unethical and corrupt researcher as the person who devised the technique. You''d also need more than one lifetime to do this, so you''d have to set up a multigenerational lab to do the experiment with your dungeon or wherever one is keeping the human subjects, who would probably not be happy with the experiment.\nIt''s not the sort of thing you''re likely to randomly find in nature though. Since every culture has incest taboos, you wouldn''t see something like this going on systematically for 20 generations lacking an external agent to force it to happen.', '18 Jun ''13, 00:45', 10),
