('100074004', '100073373', 'users/117275149/taylor-57', 'yes, i believe the same stages occur when coping with the death of a loved one. At first it seems perhaps you are in a dream state when you learn that a loved one is going to die. Second, you become angry at the world and maybe even with God. Once you have released that anger you begin to sacrifice anything or do anything to make your loved one stay with you. Then, it hits you that you are in fact powerless in this struggle with the simple and frightening idea of death, and you become depressed. Finally, maybe years later after the actual death has occurred, you can accept that maybe your loved one is in a better place and it was their time to leave this earth.', '19 Jun ''13, 18:22', 1),
