('100074496', '100062184', 'users/121545305/laurie-10', 'I have had the introvert/extrovert discuss with several friends and colleagues, and what we agreed upon was that extroverts get energized by being with other people and introverts get drained and need to recharge after being with other people.  One particular woman I know insisted that she was an introvert, yet was always quick to raise her hand and add to discussion, in fact was very talkative - as much as me, in fact.  We debated her self-evaluation (part of a job search program that did various personality tests such as True Colours, Myers-Briggs, etc) and I was certain that she was an extrovert.  She was not shy at all, but the determining factors for her considering herself an introvert were that she preferred her own company and doing solitary activities, and that although she enjoyed being around people - always needed some time alone afterwards to find balance and recharge.  I, on the other hand, always get more energy from being around people, than I do alone, and if by my self too long, find my energy depletes.  However, that does not mean I like crowds - in fact I only like crowds if I''m standing in front of them, or well back away from them.', '20 Jun ''13, 11:32', 0),
