('100075014', '100070675', 'users/120201501/aarati', 'That is exactly what they did not want to do. \nIn an experimental study , you would already know , that there are two groups ; Experimental Group and Control Group. And it has been deduced that they are treated equally. Hence , while distributing the participants in a  group , they are not distributed upon their caffeine habits or their being a male or female. Everyone is treated the same and so they are distributed , in this case , by a flip of a coin. Flipping a coin is a pretty random method.\nWell frankly speaking , initially even I did think that distributing people in groups of people who drink more coffee than the others should have been the correct option. But then I realized that this was a grouping assignment for an experimental study , where the participants are treated equal.', '21 Jun ''13, 09:55', 8),
