('100077112', '100073373', 'users/118592416/catalina-1', 'I believe the context of death and the personality traits of the ones left behind influence the stages that they go through and the sequence. For example, if your really old grandfather  was ill for a long period of time and the doctors already said there is nothing to be done, you start accepting the outcome before his death. There is no denial and no bargain because at old age we are expecting this outcome. On the other hand, if you were one of the 20-25% babies with an avoidant attachment style, you might not experience all the stages as you have always kept yourself apart from everybody.', '24 Jun ''13, 06:12', 1),
