('100077342', '100074838', 'users/120755035/tina-26', 'The spinal cord  connects the brain to the nerves throughout the body. Simply put, the brain interprets all of the information we receive from our senses and internal organs, processes them, then tells our body how to react. For example, if your hand touches a hot stove, your brain will tell your body to move your hand away as quickly as possible. So where does the spinal cord enter into the picture? Well, the spinal cord acts as the main conduit between the brain and the body.\n\nhttp://www.brainandspinalcord.org/spinal-cord-injury/the-role-of-the-spinal-cord.html', '24 Jun ''13, 14:02', 1),
