('100077636', '100073352', 'users/122497584/irene-21', 'I think dad and mom were 23 and 21 years old when they married, respectively.\nThis did not differ significantly from when I married (1st time) because I was already out of the house and financially independent.\nYes, there is a shift (marrying later) in the age people get married compared to previous generations.  I think this is due to both parties taking time to pursue an education, build careers, and/or create economic stability in preparation for building a family.\nIf I can''t imagine a life without my future spouse, then it is one indication I am ready to get married.  Entering my 2nd marriage felt so right compared to my 1st (a benefit of hindsight).', '24 Jun ''13, 22:13', 1),
