('100080790', '100074553', 'users/116393908/lucas-87', 'What about "no-gender" or gender-neutral schools? There is a BBC news here talking about a sweden''s pre-school that aims to "free children from social expectations based on their sex". I also read about others similar schools.\nI don''t think it can be a "bad thing", I think it is great to deal with gender differences in school, and also in society, in a "more free way", respecting people that differ from "ideal" gender attitudes and limiting the "gender pressure". But are not women and man "concrete" things, so pretending there are no differences at all between them is really the best way to "educate" children? Couldn''t it be negative to children self identity in the future?', '30 Jun ''13, 08:17', 3),
