('100081115', '100080938', 'users/123238013/raghu-12', 'I don''t think this is true for a number of reasons:\n1) The body uses sleep to reset hormonal balances and levels of certain physiologically important chemicals\n2) The body repairs itself (as sleep provides an immobile, nondemanding state, best for repair)\n3) The body grows during sleep more effectively\n4)  Sleep allows the body to conserve energy resources as well as consolidate and metabolize those acquired during daytime\nWhile the mind might need it more, sleep is still critical to the body''s development and function. Hope this helped!', '30 Jun ''13, 19:15', 6),
