('100081201', '100076931', 'users/117285039/juliana-8', 'Good question!  During pregnancy,  enough  time for a high cerebral performance  is neccesary. So, a premature birth would result in a baby which didn''t have develop the entire functions and it depends of the month of the birth. I mean, for example at six month of pregnancy, the fetus "  has a primitive type of memory and conscious behavior emerge. You may notice the fetus reacts more to some noises and music than others." If a baby borns before that time,  that skill would be absent . Go to this website and you would find more information.\nhttps://www.dana.org/news/brainhealth/detail.aspx?id=10050   \nI hope that could helps you', '30 Jun ''13, 22:23', 0),
('100081213', '100074447', 'users/117285039/juliana-8', 'Well, I think that the babies have the awareness to know their own body, because before the birth, they can play with their legs, hands, fingers etc, so, that''s why I say that your mother''s hypothesis isn''t true.\nOn the other hand, about the irrational fears, I say that there are many situations which leaves a trace in your life,  independently if you are  conscious or unconscious. May be, the baby could  face some dangerous situations and it would be so stressing that the emotion and the memory of this moment  had to be captured by the unconscious, but each time that happens something similar to, the reaction of fear, anxiety or whatever,  will be the same, even, like the first time thai it happened,  and he / her wouldn''t know why.', '30 Jun ''13, 22:59', 0),
