('100081420', '100073105', 'users/123533205/constantin-14', 'I think that this fact has not only a social but also a biological side to view at.\nShy men and women probably tend to live a life with fewer risks and be do not strictly follow their own interest e.g. career, so men as former caretakers of the family (fincially or more back in time ...) want to see their future (work) in safe hands before wanting kids, and woman may tend to have children much earlier to have their biological function fullfieled (their brain may let them act based on this idea) as they get older theprobability to find a man or have children may decrees. Also the society has supported the idea of women getting childs early (leads to more ?). But i think  juliern and catalina have their points,too.  I hope my rational thoughts (i am not fully convinced of my own ideas here) do not offend anyone ( would consider myself a shy person). But i do hope my thoughts can help you understand and create your own thougths.\nConstantin', '01 Jul ''13, 09:11', 1),
('100081445', '100081384', 'users/100097087/rachel-anand', 'I would say that Without an axon, there would need to be many more Neurons, which results in more synapse and neurotransmitters and the like. \nA good way to think about this is to envision a train- the time you use taking a few, longer train lines to your destination is most probably shorter than if you took many short train lines. Also, you risk losing your baggage the more lines you take. In the same way, you would risk losing the stimuli if you lose enough action potentials (considering the all or none effect. )', '01 Jul ''13, 09:59', 2),
('100081453', '100081215', 'users/100097087/rachel-anand', 'The question is asking which are variables that influence drug use/abuse. \nThere is a Video on drug reinforcers, which are any drug that produces effects that result in the person taking the drug again. So drugs of abuse are "positive reinforcers", because they make you want to take them. (Factors influencing this don''t have to be biological alone, they can also be social) \nYou can find more on the subject around the "why do people take drugs" section of the videos:)', '01 Jul ''13, 10:11', 1),
