('100082041', '100073352', 'users/117347320/amy-70', 'My parents were both 22 when they got married and they are still together 44 years later.  My husband and I were 23, almost 24.  We had been together almost 10 years when we got married and just celebrated our 10 year wedding anniversary.  \nI think the age has changed because people want to be more established and also because people are more wary of divorce.\nI know that I got married young, but we had already been together almost 10 years when we got married, had lived together and were settling into our careers.  We saw no reason to wait.  We enjoyed the first years of married life kid free and now we are enjoying our family with our two daughters.', '02 Jul ''13, 10:32', 1),
