('100082230', '100081962', 'users/118578353/susan-snycerski', 'Good question. A "crash" is when the person can no longer physically stay awake and operate normally. The body simply cannot stay awake indefinitely, and it will shut down when it reaches that point. Given that the body has depleted its energy stores, it attempts to restore through this crash episode. People may also experience depression, anxiety, over an overall uncomfortableness after a "speed run" and, unfortunately, many will seek out the drug again to reduce the discomfort they are experiencing. I hope this helps!', '02 Jul ''13, 15:27', 3),
