('100082590', '100081822', 'users/119655299/mangesh-4', 'Take first letter of each item in the list and make words that can form a grammatically correct sentence. Here it will be ''make early call to find Sada in Vicky''s bed''. I tried to make words as matching to the original words as possible. e.g. Sada=soda, Vicky=vitamin, bed=bread. This also enables me to recall words in the exact sequence.\nAnother trick: Since it is a grocery list, we can imagine a recipe made out of items, however bad it might taste! By this route we enable our imagination and chemical senses to help in remembering process. e.g. Pour milk in a vessel on a stove, break some eggs into it, add flour mixed with soda, let it boil, then put the batter on a bread, garnish it with cut tomato and cheese. This is nutritious, has lots of vitamins, but tastes horrible. Let''s go and eat ice-cream instead!', '03 Jul ''13, 03:22', 4),
