('100086333', '100085970', 'users/100000364/michael-button', 'I also think it is a combination of both.  I might agree with Chomsky on the first language but on following languages not so much.  I''m fluent in English and German.  Since English was my first language I could say I discovered it.  I learned German in school but really got fluent after living in Germany.  I have always had a ''tic'' for languages.  In the Army I learned to recognize different European and Slavic languages.  Coming from Southern California I was also exposed to Spanish but I never got fluent.  I only use it when I''m on vacation.  For some reason I can read it better than speak or understand the spoken word.\nP.S.  I agree with Leonardo on Lauren.  :-)', '09 Jul ''13, 07:34', 0),
