('100086425', '100071680', 'users/100020586/sabine-miehlbradt', 'Smiles is actually the measure here, not the variable.\nTo compare.: say you put a pot of water  on the stove with one of those 0 - 3 knobs to regulate the power output and switch on the stove  and measure the temperature on a thermometer.\nThe independent variable would be the power output, it''s measure the knob position.\nThe dependent variable would be the temperature of the water, it''s measure the thermometer reading\nAnd we would be seeing a lot more of Andy because this course would be Introduction to Physics.', '09 Jul ''13, 11:21', 0),
