('100089022', '100078992', 'users/105298481/bonifacio', 'Should students be taught about experiments that are now known to be unethical?\n\nIn my opinion, yes. Now that the damage is done, there''s no reason for us to throw away the results we achieved through the experiment. And I think people should know that there are things they should NOT do.\n\nThis is a general ethics question thread. Secondary questions: If the benefits of the research outweigh the short-term consequences, does that make the research ethical?\n\nNo. The results achieved through some experiment do not make it ethical just because they bring some benefits. Again, they may be benefical in some way, but this isolated fact doesn''t make them ethical. \n\nIs there any general way to repeat an unethical study ethically? What is forbidden to research due to morality?\n\nI don''t think so. And I do not see a reason to repeat an experiment.', '13 Jul ''13, 19:36', 3),
