('100089987', '100089926', 'users/111144077/micbaingmailcom', 'Yes.  Smiling does make me feel happier.  It''s a small but noticeable effect, which is why I like to smile! Of course, I''ve conditioned myself, and I''m attuned to my current state of face  ... so if I''m smiling I''m anticipating  I''m in a happy state.  \nHowever, it''s a stretch to say "smiling makes me happy".   It does improve the current "happiness" level for me by perhaps ~.5 on a ten point scale.\nUsing smiling "to make myself feel better" doesn''t work so well for me as smiling is not  100% conscious effort and it''s usually not the action of smiling but underlying thoughts initiating the action.  I''m usually feeling happy, and so I typically don''t smile as much when not feeling as good...and I try to keep my smiles congruent to my actual mood and do not try to fake myself or others out.', '15 Jul ''13, 16:27', 0),
