('100090178', '100083958', 'users/100212701/', 'I think NO and YES. Some emotional pain is unconditional - bad feelings if you see dead, bad smelling animal or dirty, bad smelling water in the pool, but most often this pain is the reason of self education and value building. Main source of such things is generalisation and negative results(pain) prediction.  So eaten by mistake tasty meat for vegan is conditional punishment, guilt - is also one kind of fear - you know (fear) that your behaviour can result in end of the social connection with someone + sometime "feel his or her pain". Feeling  pain of another person is possible conditional pain (I''ve never seen it in babies).', '15 Jul ''13, 23:42', 0),
