('100091374', '100090232', 'users/128570055/arlene-2', 'First off, you don''t ''unlearn'' anything.  The nature of our brains is that information that is learned generally doesn''t go away.  It can, however, be modified, which is essentially what you''re talking about.  And yes, this modification in how we think, and our behaviors is extremely important, and generally the only way of changes or improving ourselves.', '18 Jul ''13, 04:12', 2),
('100091377', '100089472', 'users/128570055/arlene-2', 'Drugs are often pushed because of pharmaceutical kickbacks.  You must be very careful when it comes to this.  Drugs very infrequently help with these matters, and if you dig into the research this is what you''ll find.  There are psychological disorders (schizophrenia, or bi-polar) where they are absolutely necessary!!!  But for most depression related psychological ''pain'' they are most certainly not.  The idea of modifying behaviors is far more relevant and effective than any drug, and it comes about through different kinds of therapy.', '18 Jul ''13, 04:17', 2),
