('100095699', '100093414', 'users/100000364/michael-button', 'I experienced the effects of sustained stress.  I had been working as a project manager on a project where I was not only in charge of the project management but also the main programmer for a project segment that was having the most problems.  I was working for 12 to 16 hours a day for a period of about 6 months.  As the technical part of the project was solved and things were running, I got sick.  I couldn''t keep any food down, developed trembling periods and heart palpitations.  My wife sent me to the hospital, where I stayed for about a week.  They made a lot of tests but found absolutely nothing wrong.  After a week in the hospital almost all symptoms were gone.\nI can only attribute this to stress.', '27 Jul ''13, 06:19', 0),
