('100097818', '100092474', 'users/100083008/geannie', 'Since birth, I''ve been up when the sun comes up, and I start getting sleepy when the sun goes down.  That wakefulness when the sun comes up and sleepiness when it starts going down is very problematic when trying to work around a night shift or a graveyard shift.  However, after working for three years in a graveyard shift, I learned that as long as I can manipulate the light, I can "trick" my body into thinking it''s up and down at the "right" times.  I''m definitely not at my best though.  \nThere''s a clear improvement when I''m able to follow the sun''s 24-hour cycle.  Unfortunately, that only happens during vacation time anymore, but I find it interesting just how quickly my body will adjust to that particular cycle.  Adjusting from it to any deviation is much more difficult.', '31 Jul ''13, 13:46', 0),
