('100098837', '100098543', 'users/112078261/tauheed-1', 'it does seem that these stats are incomplete. The formula implied here is:  RR=KC/KP (RR= Relative risk of dying in a crash when embarking on a car trip vs plane trip , KC=number killed in car accidents; KP = number killed in plane accidents). The correct formula would seem to be: RR=(KC/NC)/(KP/NP) where NC = number of car trips, NP= number of plane trips.  in the simple case (i.e. including all car trips, even trips to the grocery store), it would seem that car trips are far safer than plane trips (contrary to what is said in the video). Things get more complicated if certain types of car trips (e.g.  through dangerous intersections; if the car trip is with a cautious driver vs an aggressive driver) have significantly higher risk of dying than other types of car trips.', '02 Aug ''13, 10:24', 2),
