l. In my opinion one of the strongest reasons is reproductivity function. I predict that you want to say that love doesn''t have any common with reproductivity. But in some sense it''s wrong. For example brother and sister could love each other, but marriage between them is banned because their children would be weak, ugly and so on. But unlike "family love" gays completely don''t have any children. The definition of species from Wiki: "A species is often defined as a group of organisms capable of interbreeding and producing fertile offspring". Another reasons you could find in google or I''ve found this link.\nGood luck, Sylvia, I hope you have a nice day. And don''t forget about smiling, it''s good for everyone ;).', '02 Aug ''13, 11:20', 1),
('100098984', '100098864', 'users/128813419/giuliana', 'This is how I understood it as well (but of course I am not sure!) The blue terminal button is at the end of the axon, and this is the output of a cell (the way a neuron transmits signals to other neurons). Signals are received by symmetrical buttons which are on dendrites (but Lauren does not say this explicitly); hence I understand that dendrites are the input device (they receive signals sent by other neurons); so the green button in the figure should be a dendrite''s button.', '02 Aug ''13, 16:28', 0),
('100098988', '100081384', 'users/128813419/giuliana', 'If I understood correctly (of which of course I am not sure), the axon is an output device (sends information to other neurons), while the dendrites are input devices (receive information from other neurons). I developed this idea because they say that information is passed by means of the neurotransmitters, and these are chemicals released by the axon''s button; in the figures they present, these button always seem to connect to the dendrites, and hence I guess that these are input devices, even though they never say it explicitly.  Using the same buttons for input and output would probably cause confusion in signal transmission and slow down the operation instead of speeding it up.', '02 Aug ''13, 16:38', 2),
