('100099730', '100096191', 'users/113287159/luis-125', 'I also believe that if you don''t have a word for it, you can always understand that concept.\nNevertheless, it could be very difficult to grasp a concept if you lack the necessary vocabulary, because the concept needs to be explained in others more general terms, or with physical actions as metaphors.\nAnd it could get worse, for example, trying to explain an abstract concept based on other abstract concepts.\nSo, it could be very difficult, but there''s always a possibility.\nProbably we could communicate with a lot fewer words, but when we try to understand or communicate more complex things, using the same words over and over again could become tiresome and incredible complex.\nInstead, we create new words, so we could communicate our needs more effectively for that moment and environment.\nSo it''s important to learn a lot of vocabulary, if possible in many languages, to have more building blocks for understanding and expressing more complex concepts.', '04 Aug ''13, 14:28', 1),
