('100100307', '100089779', 'users/118076567/diego-114', 'Well, if the bouba/kiki effect was true, you would probably be able to easily identify these pairs of sylables in Japanese, right?\n\n\nOne is mamoo, the other keki. Which is which?', '05 Aug ''13, 19:13', 3),
('100100316', '100093166', 'users/118076567/diego-114', 'My native language is Portuguese, but when I was living in Canada, most of my dreams were in English, and I asked other foreigners about it and, suprisingly to me,  most of them said they never had dreams in English.\nI have had dreams in Spanish, Italian, French, and English (all languages that I studied at least for a few months). I also had a dream where I was in a Japanese class, but at the time I didn''t know Japanese (which I only started studying much later) and I couldn''t understand anything people said in the dream. What language was that after all? Were the people  just babbling random sounds that sounded Japanese to me?  Or was it real Japanese I caught unconsciously by, say,  watching movies and listening to songs? I guess I will never know...', '05 Aug ''13, 19:43', 2),
