('100100690', '100091660', 'users/117588655/julirn', 'Hello!\nWhile I think this is a nice movie, I do not think that a soldier that has no fear at all would be a good soldier. \nA soldier without fear would not likely protect himself and likely take (probably unnecessary) risks in a near-suicidal manner. He would likely commit war crimes, having no fear of prosecution. He would probably not fear to disregard orders if they don''t fit him without fear of punishment. - All this might be arguments against such a "killing machine". \nGru\nJulien Caussin', '06 Aug ''13, 15:38', 3),
