('100100802', '100092655', 'users/119146441/sarah-129', 'These issues are rarely that black and white. Many of the animals were bred in captivity and raised in captivity, so for them, the laboratory IS their habitat. And animals living in captivity often live longer and healthier lives than those in the wild. Cali, for instance, would never have survived if not for animal husbandry and psychology. I agree that these situations often raise ethical questions, but it does not do to only look at it from one point of view.', '06 Aug ''13, 19:11', 2),
