('100100977', '100093944', 'users/100072346/dawn-kua', 'People with Narcolepsy often don''t produce enough Hypocretin. There is a theory now that it may be an auto-immune disease. As it''s a rare disease, there''s still a lot of research ongoing about this. If you know someone with Narcolepsy though, they should talk to their doctors as there are drugs out there that can help and they make a LOT of difference. A lot of narcoleptics have described it as finally being awake for the first time.', '07 Aug ''13, 05:29', 2),
