('100101213', '100100635', 'users/117588655/julirn', 'Hello!\nI must admit that I didn''t describe it quite well... My point that large parts of Germany, after World War II, were in ruins. According to Maslow, the Germans should have worked only to build shelters and to feed themselves. But this was not the case, for example, cinemas were running immediately after the war. - And this behavior is one thing that can be observed nowadays in slums all over the world. \nDid I describe my point now more accurate?\nGru\nJulien Caussin', '07 Aug ''13, 15:49', 1),
