('100102253', '100101946', 'users/132497163/saleh-6', 'You are right, the placebo may affect the results. But this can be a good thing. If the group who had the decaf showed a decrease in the reaction time just like the group with the caffeine, then we can say that the decrease in the reaction time is not necessarily due to the caffeine but can be due to our conviction that coffee does that.\nIn other words, this would be interpreted as,\n"whether we drink coffee or something else and we are convinced it will make us more alert, then it will."', '09 Aug ''13, 15:32', 3),
