('100102563', '100093414', 'users/100085032/christian-wolpert', 'For me, I usually don''t get ill during stressful times but immediately after the stress has calmed down (just like Michael Button described before). So, for example, I regularly get ill during my winter holidays, after having tried everything possible to finish the assignments at work before my leave. But as soon as I think I''m done and can relax, I catch a flue...\nDuring the phase of accute stress, I suspect my immune system is even more active than normal. It''s almost like I''m too stressed to get ill - since this would probably even create more stress! \nMichael and I are not the only ones who made this experience. I heard this is called "Leisure Sickness": http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leisure_Sickness\nWhat do you think about this, Lauren?', '10 Aug ''13, 13:31', 0),
