('100102994', '100093874', 'users/118076567/diego-114', 'I had an experience that illustrates my point of view on the subject.\nI used to work in a huge book store chain and had just an average wage. But I really liked what I did, dealing with books and people all day and had more than enough time to see friends and enjoy life. I used to go work so motivated that my production was way better than that of my coworkers, so my manager offered me a lot more hours, doing different tasks in a different crazy schedule. It meant more money, so I didn''t think twice. After a couple of months, I was always tired, couldn''t see my friends so often, and when I was at home all I wanted to do was sleep. The extra money didn''t make much difference anymore in my overall personal satisfaction. My motivation was gone and my production went down. After a while I got frustrated and eventually quit my job.', '11 Aug ''13, 20:58', 4),
