('100106702', '100102233', 'users/132657376/alina-25', 'Shyness is a feature of character that is generally treated as "negative" by both men and women. Shy men encounter more difficulties in life than shy women. In some cultures women are even preferred to be shy and obedient, whereas men tend to be active, assertive, sociable and independent in all aspects of life. If a man is shy you can assume that he has some problems in his personal life. Shy men are often less sociable and friendly , they fear to be rejected by women. As a result, they can even experience troubles with sex. Shy women tend to find a partner as sooner as possible to get rid of the complex of shyness, because with a partner she feels much more comfortable, self-confident and attractive towards the opposite sex.', '24 Aug ''13, 01:14', 4),
