('100107379', '100092655', 'users/119146441/sarah-129', 'If we want to let nature do its duty we might as well wipe the human race off the surface of the planet. Otherwise we''d just be going about our business, ignoring the real effects of our actions, and destroying species without at least an effort to preserve them. Whatever faults keeping animals in captivity has, at least the animals stay alive. Has anyone here read Life of Pi? He''s not kidding about the zoo stuff, you know. Please think about what you''re saying. Telling people how emphatically you think something is wrong means nothing except that you''re choosing to go with a trend that showcases how fantastic your morals are. If you actually have a realistic suggestion for some concrete action that might be taken, by all means share it. I''ll be the last one to say that animal captivity is right or that we shouldn''t take care of our natural environment--we only have one earth and all that--trust me, I was in this mob not that long ago, I know your arguments, I''ve written speeches with them--but I believe that I have no right to whine if I''m not doing something about it. I''m sorry if I''m getting a tad snarky, but I dislike uninformed complaining and it''s really early in the morning. These things really are complicated, so have simple THIS IS JUST WRONG rants is probably the only thing that''s just wrong.', '26 Aug ''13, 08:05', 0),
