('100111373', '100100377', 'users/100041877/robin-4', 'One example of a token economy that adults can use comes from well-known comedian Jerry Seinfeld. One technique that Seinfeld used early in his career to foster the habit of writing every day was to mark each day he wrote with an X on a calendar. As the chain grows with daily activity you become more proud of its growth, and you develop motivation to not "break the chain."  Its a visual form of token that I''ve found actually works for my own motivation. There''s more on it here: http://lifehacker.com/281626/jerry-seinfelds-productivity-secret', '07 Sep ''13, 22:25', 3),
('100111415', '100066674', 'users/100002514/anurag-acharya', 'Biological Psychology focuses on how the chemical or biological factors affect a person and/or his/her behavior and thought-process. As the study is psychology, it obviously is mostly focuses in the nervous system and the chemical (and otherwise) composition of the brain.\nClinical Psychology can be understood as primarily the application of the various psychological understandings and knowledge to help a person who has any kind of disorder whose primary cause if psychological factors. Basically, all the "shrinks" people see are clinical psychologists.\nAnd of course, if we go a bit deeper, it all comes together as all sub-fields are psychology are interlinked. So it is better to understand various sub-fields of psychology as several chapters of a book rather than several separate volumes.\nHope I was clear!', '08 Sep ''13, 03:53', 1),
