('100113445', '100112767', 'users/137451550/vivien-1', 'I''m not really an expert in this, but I remembered from my biology class in high school that it basically also means that there are huge possibility that both of your parents actually has recessive alleles of brown eyes. Something in a simple way is that if we put your parents genes, with dominant B (blue) and recessive b (brown):\nBb + Bb =\nBB (dominant blue)\nBb (Dominant blue with recessive brown)\nbB (Dominant blue with recessive brown)\nbb (both recessive brown, but in absence of dominant, they became the visible trait)\nIn this case, your mother is clearly carries the recessive brown, but perhaps so does your father but just never showed up in his family so far.', '15 Sep ''13, 06:36', 0),
('100113469', '100112767', 'users/100242519/marcel-feenstra', '@vivien-1:\nIn the "normal case", it is actually the other way round: brown is dominant, blue recessive; cf.:\nhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/gcsebitesize/science/21c/genes/genetic_diseasesrev1.shtml\n(Of course, that doesn''t explain Sarah''s situation; that''s why I referred to the "normal" case... :-b)', '15 Sep ''13, 09:00', 0),
('100113591', '100112767', 'users/119544651/konfou', 'It puzzles you because using the eye color is a bad dominant/recessive example. It certainly is the easier for people to think on terms of, but that doesn''t change the fact that it is flawed. The eye color is determined by many genes, and the precise color depends on two distinct factors (first being the pigmentation of the iris, and the second is the way in which the stroma of iris scatters the light rays).\nYou say that your color changed when you''re 9. That is strange, since most changes occur during the first, but sometimes up to three, years of age. Your situation is still debated for whether chemical reactions can result in observable changes to the eye color past those years.\nUnfortunately that is all I know, so I will refer you for more at http://genetics.thetech.org/ask/ask29. Alternatively you can try different keywords combination on Google.', '15 Sep ''13, 16:09', 1),
