('100113730', '100110460', 'users/100304477/ampharos', 'Yes, why are we only questioned about ''the positive side'' of the spectrum? (Needless to say, my big 5 test made me feel just a little bit sad... xD)\nOne think that I see neurotic people are good at is making protocols. (For example, I volunteer at a small library and the majority of people there have a shift once every two weeks, so good communication is key. We got tons of great, detailed protocols, ranging from all the steps of opening the shop to what we should do in case a guest has a hypo (diabetes)). \nNeurotics may also be good programmers (my code is always loaded with exception handlers and comments, in case of stupid users or readers).', '16 Sep ''13, 06:51', 1),
