('100113777', '100101840', 'users/118076567/diego-114', 'After I read your comments, I looked for material that would add other versions of the story.\nYes, the NY Times article seem to be exaggerated, there weren''t 38 people at their windows just watching Ms. Genovese being killed, but, still, there were some people who heard screams and thought they were nothing serious. Even if the story didn''t happen exactly how it''s usually told, I don''t see any reason why it should not be used as an example of the bystander effect. \nIt seems that you are giving a  single source of information more validity than any other, undeservedly dismissing Genovese''s story as a mere myth, which is certainly not.', '16 Sep ''13, 11:20', 2),
