('100114023', '100112474', 'users/100238151/christian-nyumbayire', 'If there are lots of people around you and the situation require to you all to help someone, the perceived responsibility will be lower than in the case where fewer people witnessed, because distributed among you all. Lots of people will do nothing, supposing others could do in their place what should be done. I think in the end it''s just a question of perceived costs and benefits. People prefer to not take responsibilities without personal gains.', '17 Sep ''13, 05:29', 0),
('100114032', '100112767', 'users/147760327/jehonas', 'Hi,\n I liked Konfou''s answer. Also the link he gave is one I have been always referring to when having questions about genetics.  They also used to have an eye- color - calculator. The change of color is not rare, but the age in which it occurred is. I was also born with green eyes which turned to brown and straight hair which turned to curly. But, these changes happened before I was 2.', '17 Sep ''13, 06:29', 0),
