('100115255', '100083676', 'users/132657376/alina-25', 'For ethical reasons Dr. Watson''s experiment on classical conditioning of fear is awful and unacceptable. It caused a serious psychological trauma for Albert and he had never extinguished his fear. As for me, I suffer from musophobia and I can''t extinguish this fear. Sometimes my boyfriend makes me watch at the pictures of rats and mice to get rid of my fear, but as a result my fear gets stronger and stronger. I realize that my phobia may seem rather silly, but for me it is real stress:-)', '22 Sep ''13, 05:02', 0),
('100115332', '100113639', 'users/125984079/dieter-9', 'The instructors got the scale wrong. To get into the math of it, you can look at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decibel.\nDecibels, abbreviated by dB are using in many engineering disciplines. When we talk about the volume of the sound, we talk about the power in the sound wave. The dB is derived from the logarithm base 10.\nA decrease of 10dB means that we have only 1/10th the power (i.e. volume; not half as stated). The change for a factor in power of two is roughly 3dB.\nLoud noise (see the link here that has examples) could for example have 100dB.  This is 10^10 or 10000000000 (10 Billion) times as much power falling on our ears as what we get at 0dB, the threshold of perception.', '22 Sep ''13, 15:08', 1),
