('100115733', '100102977', 'users/100104209/marcus', 'I can understand sex as a physiological need when considered like excretion(sperms or ova). Otherwise when seen as something two people do but don''t need to "share" I''d prioritize safety, belonging and  sexual intimacy over it.\nWhat''s really missing in this hierarchy is the will to meaning as Victor Frankl put it. Whereby it should be considered that not all people get the same chances to develop. What poor people can achieve spiritually or mentally can never outweight the possibilities wealth provides. But it''s often a cheap excuse to consolidate other hierarchies.\nM.S.', '24 Sep ''13, 11:29', 0),
