('100115965', '100098858', 'users/100104209/marcus', 'When you imagine wandering up your spine and looking at the truncus cerebri (stem) you will notice the parts Medulla, Pons and Mesencephalon(middle brain). \nAt the same time you can also say, the middle brain does not belong to the parts "behind"(hindbrain). The hindbrain is rather including Pons and Medulla and of course a part which is not in the line of the spine but somehow like a knot at its back: the cerebellum. you wouldn''t come up with the idea to see that as a part of the stem(truncus cerebri).\nNow what is the fore brain(Prosencephalon)? In the beginnings of your development it has been at the very front, but by now has grown in the "inbetween" Diencephalon(epi-,hypo- or just thalamus) and the endbrain(Telencephalon) with its two hemispheres.\nM.S.', '25 Sep ''13, 10:38', 0),
