('100117071', '100097670', 'users/116169258/emanuele-7', 'Thank you everyone for your answers, I wanted to add something to the discussion. Recently I''ve seen a video called "Developers and Depression".\nIt''s a very good talk, and I suggest everyone to watch it.  Around minute 7, Greg talks about a book he read:\nThe Edison Gene: ADHD and the Gift of the Hunter Child.\nIn this book, they identify two different types of people: hunters and farmers. Hunters keep shifting attention, farmers are methodical and meticulous. They argue that modern society favours today the farmers type. \nLinear thinkers vs non-linear thinkers. Non-linear thinkers focus in situations of stress and danger.\nIn modern society, we don''t face those types of situations much, but rather we need to show up on time, be meticulous...\nLater on, Greg says that the software industry is more accepting of the hunter personality, it''s often ok to wake up late, be productive at night, having long periods of poor productivity followed by burst of hyperactivity.\nThis talk has explained to me how hunters and farmers are both present in the industry. Perhaps: implementers and maintainers? \nThe point of the talk though, is that as a whole an extreme hunter type of personality is less productive, and faces social problems and even bigger risks of suicide.\nMedical help is available, through drugs and psychotherapy if the very hard first step of searching for help is taken.', '01 Oct ''13, 08:07', 0),
