('100117290', '100113275', 'users/105298481/bonifacio', 'Could we say that the external factors such as economic, social and\nhistoric situation influences our family and its functioning leading\nto differences in the ways we are reared?\n\nYes.\n\nOr are talking about the social interactions with people out of\nfamily? I mean, how our inside the family experiences may be less important\nthan the outside experiences to shape personality?\n\nJust consider that you spend most of your time away from your family. Especially in early age, you spend most of your time in school and with your friends, surrounded by people who are not part of your family. Also, there are much more people that don''t belong to your family than people that do.\nSo, you are in constant contact with people that are not your family members (more than you are with people that are part of your family) and these are the people with who you spend more time with.', '01 Oct ''13, 22:04', 0),
