('100120440', '100099952', 'users/154020240/sandra-89', 'I think that is a good point and yet the other side is a lot of people don''t ever choose to have difficult feelings that they may have and may not know the right method to dealing with them, even though others will handle the same situation as a much better experience.  \nYet I would say though that if a person is going through a really hard psychological experience, and in some way they contributed to it like say falling in love with someone and getting rejected versus not having any choice like if you are being abused by an authority figure that you can''t get away from.  In the cases the person had some choice in the matter, they should ultimately face their pain because I think of it as their own negative issues coming up, otherwise the pain will probably repeat in another issue later.', '12 Oct ''13, 21:15', 0),
