('100120845', '100113634', 'users/154020240/sandra-89', 'Johann Wolfgang von Goethe studied color and also pointed out that if you put a colored light on something the shadow on one side will be the color of the light and on the other side of the shape the shadow will be perceived by our eyes as the polar of that color.  But cover up the the other shadow and your eye will see a gray shadow.  Our eyes are always filling in what we should be seeing.  \nI also find this an interesting subject.', '14 Oct ''13, 17:39', 1),
