('100121023', '100074995', 'users/154020240/sandra-89', 'No I do think atheists go through the bargaining stage.  Bargaining does not have to be begging someone or something.  That was just the example she used.  It is any kind of bargain.  Many people are willing to make sacrifices they normally wouldn''t do in hopes of staying alive longer.  Like maybe if you have lung cancer and the doctor says you are going to die, maybe you stop smoking and exercise more.  Or maybe you see more than one doctor in hopes that someone will have a different medicine that will help save your life.', '15 Oct ''13, 13:17', 0),
('100121030', '100082949', 'users/154020240/sandra-89', 'In a way I agree, because the hormones the mother experiences the baby will also be around.  A lot of fear or anger hormones may tell the baby that this is not a safe environment I will be going into.  \nBut on the other hand trying not to feel certain emotions so that you will provide a healthy environment for the child I don''t think is a good idea either.  Because in that process a person may choose to stuff their problems inside and not deal with them, and that to me sounds just as unhealthy. \nThe best thing in my opinion is just try to be happy.  If there are stressful things like financial problems just try to get them fixed as soon as one can so it is not an issue.  Also when a person is pregnant there are also hormones that make people more emotional than usual, so it is only natural that there will be some ups and downs during this time.', '15 Oct ''13, 13:54', 0),
