('100122328', '100098583', 'users/122995937/andy-177', 'Symptoms included difficulty staying focussed, difficulty controlling behaviour and hyperactivity. Surely they have got to look at changing the definition as that definition is pretty much sums up any child that I have ever observed. There has been a massive increase in the number of children diagnoised with ADHD, we should be asking why this has happened. Its unrealistic to think that every child would be able to sit peacefully in a classroom all day, to me to expect that is not normal. Parents should really think twice if not three times about medicating their kids and instead look at different ways of stimulating them.', '20 Oct ''13, 18:54', 0),
