('100122380', '100096191', 'users/132657376/alina-25', 'In each language there are a lot of words that don''t have a direct translation in the other language. For example, in my mother''s tongue we don''t have one word for "grandparents". We have to say "grandmother and grandfather". Nowadays, due to globalization native languages are abundant with the loanwords and we perfectly understand them. It''s different when we deal with "lacunas", nationally determined, specific element of the culture, which found a reflection in the language of the native speakers, and which cannot be totally understood by the foreigners. To understand the meaning of these concepts, you should learn more information about their speakers, their culture and way of life.', '21 Oct ''13, 04:06', 1),
