('100123035', '100122702', 'users/157252647/jayalakshmi', 'From what I understood,I think they conducted a study to check the effects of meditation on brain tissue growth in the regions of emotional processing and understanding.Firstly as they were trying to establish a cause and effect relationship,it was an experimental study.Secondly the two groups that were formed were the same except that one was exposed to meditation and the other was not.Hence,meditation is the independent variable. Then they were trying to conclude if meditation has an effect on the brain tissue growth.,i.e they were studying the resultant brain tissue growth in the 2 groups.Thus it is clear that brain tissue growth is the dependent variable here.Finally the studies showed that the group which meditated showed a growth in their brain tissues.Therefore a cause was established. I hope this explanation helps and is what you asked for ?', '24 Oct ''13, 03:55', 2),
