('100123843', '100092474', 'users/100096925/connie-chow-petit', 'Really good question. :)\nI was a night person through and through until half a year ago. I pro-actively changed my sleep pattern to get better rest and wake up early. At first it was tough, I wanted to resist, but eventually I started to love the early morning boosts of energy. I take a short nap in the afternoons now and also have bursts of energy come sundown. It''s pretty cool to have both. I also sleep more fully and normal now which is a big bonus.\nAs for shift work, I know some people who navigate night shifts and days shifts consecutively. The key is to try to switch back to normal waking hours when you''re off to catch some sunlight, go outside and basically let your body readjust. It''s important.', '28 Oct ''13, 07:17', 0),
