('100131353', '100127202', 'users/132371680/elisabeth-16', 'The idea behind theories of birth order effect is that, to use your example, birth order influences parental attention, which in turn influences personality ... so birth order influences personality.\nIt''s a bit like saying one''s proximity to the North or South Pole influences how much one spends on winter clothes. Yes, there is a mediating variable -- average winter temperatures, in this case -- but that hardly makes the ''root cause'', as it were, irrelevant.\nThat said, the evidence for birth order''s on personality isn''t as strong as it''s often made out to be, largely due to the confounding effects of family size. You can find one brief but balanced summary on the Scientific American website.', '27 Nov ''13, 03:37', 2),
