('100134104', '100129606', 'users/180334009/francisco-185', 'I think the question is clear and so is the answer. There is not an obligation to choose random people. The independent variable introduced by the researcher is the degree of anxiety of the people in each group. There is no distinction in the group between age, gender or whatever any other characteristic, so we can assume the statistical distribution of the group would be a Normal one.\nOn the other hand, the dependent variable is a result of a test, applied equally to all the subjects of the research.\nAssuming that the measure of anxiety is obtained in the same way from all the subjects of the test, I think the experimental study could be completely valid.', '09 Dec ''13, 15:43', 0),
