('100134496', '100106811', 'users/100029839/viliam-bur', 'Sometimes the words are re-used for many meanings, so it is important to remember which meaning they have in a given context. These words probably start with one meaning, but people in other situations use them as metaphors for something, so they gradually get additional meanings in those situations.\nIn different situations, the word "negative" can mean:\n-  negative number = smaller than zero\n-  negative space = an artistically interesting space between objects\n-  negative = a photographic paper with inverted colors\n-  negative liberty = freedom from interference of other people\n-  negative change = the electrical charge of an electron\n-  something bad\nWhen speaking about conditioning in psychology, the meaning of "negative" is "by removing something". Thus, negative reinforcement means rewarding someone by removing something (that they dislike), and negative punishment means punishing someone by removing something (that they like).\nIt has absolutely no connection with bad things or with negative electric charge. :D\nI guess when people speak about conditioning, they would not use the word "negative" to mean bad behavior, because that would be confusing. They would probably just speak about the behavior without expressing judgement, or use a different word e.g. "undesired".', '11 Dec ''13, 12:08', 1),
