('100147374', '100116154', 'users/113259599/drcookie', 'An allele is just a version of a gene. In genetics the word "allele" and "mutation" can be used interchangeably. The mutation that causes Huntington''s Disease occurs in a gene. So one version (or allele) of this gene could have the mutation and another version (or a different allele) does not have the mutation.\nDoes that help?', '24 Jan ''14, 21:41', 3),
