('100148542', '100135268', 'users/124998985/andre-49', 'The study of psychology refers specifically to human psychology. Let''s look at the APA(American Pyschological Assocation)s website: http://www.apa.org/support/about/apa/psychology.aspx#answer and we''ll get the answer (quoting):\n"Psychology is the study of the mind and behavior. The discipline embraces all aspects of the human experience  from the functions of the brain to the actions of nations, from child development to care for the aged. In every conceivable setting from scientific research centers to mental healthcare services, "the understanding of behavior" is the enterprise of psychologists."\nIf we look at this definition then it refers to human psychology only. With that in mind, you should read up about Comparative Psychology (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparative_psycholoy ), that Wikipedia, for all it''s worth, lists a field of psychology.\nIt could very well be a matter of who you believe to have figured out the ''one true'' definition of the field though. At the end of the day, both sides of the coin has merit.', '28 Jan ''14, 14:51', 1),
