('100165139', '100090232', 'users/123476418/nikhilesh-3', 'When we are ''unlearning'' something, basically we''ll keep telling ourselves not to learn that thing and repeating this behavior would consequently strengthen the neurons in our brain about what ''not to learn'' rather than what should be learned. So for the sake of unlearning that thing, we are learning it more!\nThus by ''unlearning'' if you mean forgetting something, that''s not possible. Basically, ''unlearning'' is not in our hands and learning is the only option.\nHowever, if we keep learning positive things and not focus on the negative aspects repeatedly, then perhaps the neural connections of the negative behaviors would go weaker with time and vanish away. And that is why, a positive attitude to learn is the only thing required to be successful in life. Bingo!', '26 Mar ''14, 03:06', 0),
