('100184011', '100155592', 'users/287741424/annika-14', 'I once witnessed a drunken man beating his wife, who was suckling a baby at the same time, in public. A large number of people had gathered to watch but nobody did anything. The reason why nobody interfered were a) he had a right to beat his disobedient wife, the others had no legal right to intrfere as such and b) nobody wanted to become the target of the man''s blows or the revenge of his associates - losing the control of the situation would have meant certain danger for the person interfering... Being from a different culture I was unaware of the danger at the time so I took the baby away from the mother, as for it not to get beaten, and only then the locals found a win-win solution that stopped the violence. \nNow that I know how that society works, would I do the same thing? Certainly not, my self-preservation instinct (fear of getting hurt) is stronger than my sense of right and wrong!', '19 May ''14, 19:22', 1),
