('100184691', '100123455', 'users/100104209/marcus', 'I think it''s good comment "foppington" made. \nIn the course here, altruism stands somehow related to Kin-selection, Reciprocal altruism and Love.\nI somehow missed a thing which is closely connected to love but is not really the same. I too had to think about Eriksons state of generativity but I also remembered Frankl. So I kept missing some sort of humanistic, maybe transcendental state Viktor Frankl would have called "meaning". This kind of altruism resulting out of meaning is not so much dependent on what other people might give you as a reward, nor is it concentrated on what you contribute towards your kin and it is also not exactly love in a narrow sense.\nAnd last but not least empathy doesn''t have to be connecte do this kind of meaningful altruism. It better is, but it needn''t be.', '22 May ''14, 02:23', 0),
