('100185436', '100163439', 'users/291450109/gordon-85', 'If we are constrained to damage-free analysis of how the brain works, then we need to leverage either non-intrusive techniques like Functional Magnetic Resonance Imaging (fMRI) or misadventure--natural or provoked. The former is leading to detailed maps of what, where, and when the various parts of the brain are used. The later treats the brain like an arbitrary input-output system, and often was the by-product of war (-like) conditions or "sanatoriums". Now we have Geneva Conventions Drug testing standards and Ethics committees to prevent deliberate misadventure!', '24 May ''14, 21:06', 1),
