('100198646', '100099922', 'users/100104209/marcus', 'dangerous doesn''t make sense.\nYour thinking can be slow. So it''s working (functional, though it may be doing an extra mile while finding the solution), it may even be normal in the statistical sense(no deviation, because most people don''t think about what you think..so they might not be as trained in a special task) and it need not be to your distress(others might not mind, you might not notice or feel bad because no one told you so far) and last but not least you need not be a danger to others. \nTalking about the general and specific I agree that the term dysfunctional is more specific as there can be a continuum from "disturbance" to dysfunction. In dysfunction you''re not just disturbed in a function. An underlying process might be affected.', '25 Jun ''14, 16:59', 0),
