('100199497', '100101946', 'users/137470381/prudhvi-1', 'The main point is to measure how the drug caffeine affects response times. Giving them a decaf to the group 2 makes them emotionally equivalent to group 1. Therefore reaction time to mood is eliminated. However, one thing that is not taken in consideration. Is about the people who don''t like coffee??? This number may be small so it is possible that only one group has people who don''t like coffee. And believe me when I say that if you give some one who doesn''t like coffee . The reaction is going to be bad. When I first tried coffee, I vomited, felt dizziness as my brain WAS BEING COMPRESSED. Whoa, I will never touch coffee in my life again. However, group 2 may feel not quite emotionally satisfied because I heard that decaf and the regular coffee taste different. So if they don''t have decaf every morning, they may recognize that their coffee isn''t quite right.', '27 Jun ''14, 10:24', 0),
