('100252353', '100093585', 'users/276650891/vincentm', 'In fact, there are only 6 emotions: joy, anger, sadness, fear, disgust and surprise according to Ekman. All the other states are either combinations of those basic emotions or not emotions at all, i.e. not physiological response to external stimuli.\nI am surprised that the teachers have not mentioned the physiological aspect of emotions because it is the only deciding factor between emotions and the other affective states.', '04 Jan, 05:19', 0);
